To mock `await Promise.all()` in your test, you can use the `jest.spyOn` function to mock the implementation of `Promise.all()` and return a resolved or rejected promise. Here's an example of how you can mock `await Promise.all()` in your test:

```javascript
import { render } from '@testing-library/react';
import YourComponent from './YourComponent';

describe('YourComponent', () => {
  it('should handle Promise.all() correctly', async () => {
    // Create a mock function to replace the original Promise.all() implementation
    const mockPromiseAll = jest.spyOn(Promise, 'all');

    // Mock the resolved or rejected promises that you want to return from Promise.all()
    const resolvedPromises = [Promise.resolve('Result 1'), Promise.resolve('Result 2')];
    const rejectedPromise = Promise.reject(new Error('Error'));

    // Set the resolved or rejected promises as the return value for Promise.all()
    mockPromiseAll.mockResolvedValue(resolvedPromises); // Mock resolved promises
    // OR
    mockPromiseAll.mockRejectedValue(rejectedPromise); // Mock rejected promise

    // Render your component
    const { container } = render(<YourComponent />);

    // ...

    // Your test assertions
  });
});
```

